snippet.textDisplay: Oh and another thing I would like to call out to Bruins fans.  I've been FAITHFULLY watching the Bruins since Bobby Orr came into the league and as long as Tuukka is in net, the Bruins don't win a Cup because he totally CHOKES in the biggest games.  Yes, in game 7 of last year Cup finals, that first goal that got by him was soft.  He had a great playoff run and they don't get to the finals without him BUT he choked when it mattered most, just like in 2013.  Watch him; he stays on his knees, gets deep and small in the net, moves slowly side to side and gets beat along the posts easily.  Go back and watch those key games.  The kid at the other end of the ice in game 7 last year stole that game for the Blues when the Bruins hammered them in the first, getting nothing to show for it and then Tissue Tuukka the Turtle lets in a softie; that will take the wind out of anyone's sails, no matter what the team say publicly. They won in 2011 because the B's physically crushed the opponents (look at their D from that year) but more importantly, Tim Thomas stood on his head which motivated them to dig deep.
